Role: You are a Senior Frontend Engineer and Software Architect with expertise in React, TypeScript, and lightweight client-side state management (Zustand, Zod). You specialize in building robust, data-driven web games optimized for the Yandex Games platform.Task: Write the core architecture, TypeScript types, and a Zustand state manager for the browser game "Где ложь? Симулятор детектива". The solution must strictly separate static case data (loaded from JSON) from the runtime mutable player state.1. Architectural Rules & RequirementsData-Driven: Adding a new case or a new translation must be possible by creating/editing a single JSON file without modifying any React or Zustand logic.Yandex SDK Integration: State must prioritize Yandex Cloud Saves (ysdk.getPlayer().setData()).Offline Fallback: If the player is not authenticated or the network fails, seamlessly fallback to LocalStorage.Rate-Limit Protection (Debounce): Cloud sync must be throttled/debounced to execute a maximum of once every 10 seconds, or instantly upon mounting the ResultScreen (Case Closure).Game Pause Guard: Implement a global isPaused flag synced with Yandex Ad SDK lifecycles (onOpen and onClose) to safely mute audio contexts and freeze game progression.2. Full Data Specification & JSON Schema ReferenceYour state and types must natively support the following structural schema, including multi-language support (i18n) and evidence verification tokens:JSON{
