3. Core Logic Specifications to ImplementA. The Multi-Tier Reward Math EngineThe game reward for a correct verdict is split between the macro-decision and structural proof precision:Verdict Base Component: 50% of claimAmount (or fixed standard score reward) is allocated strictly for matching playerDecision === case.correctDecision.Evidence Proof Component: The remaining 50% scales linearly based on the exact ratio of correctly flagged contradictions:$$\text{Proof Component} = 0.5 \times \text{BaseReward} \times \left( \frac{\text{CorrectlyMarkedContradictions}}{\text{TotalContradictionsInCase}} \right)$$Anti-Cheat Penalty: If a player stamps an evidence card as a contradiction when isContradiction === false, apply a safe penalty (e.g., -50 currency units) to block brute-force click spamming.Failure State Trigger: If balance <= 0, lock progression until rewarded_ad_restore_funds callback fires, restoring balance to a standard minimum of 2000.B. The Dynamic Daily Case EvaluatorServer Time Constraint: Daily case locking and unlocking triggers must evaluate against Yandex Server Time/Network API time strings, NOT the player's mutable local device time configuration.Complexity Modifier: If case.type === 'daily', multiplier metrics apply scaling rules (reward * 5).C. Drafting & Active Save StateStore currently toggled evidence selections inside a running session container selectedEvidenceIds: string[].Ensure exiting mid-game saves the exact state to local memory, allowing the investigator to resume exactly where they left off.4. Expected Code OutputsPlease write clean, production-grade code:Strict TypeScript Interfaces: Define Case, Evidence, Language, PlayerStats, and GameStoreState.Zod Validation Schema: Create an external validation schema parser to ensure runtime imported Case JSON streams align seamlessly with data rules.Zustand Store Module: Provide the full logic slice implementation containing:Action triggers for setting active language (setLanguage).Toggling evidence items as contradictions (toggleEvidenceStamp).Submitting verdicts and evaluating rewards (submitVerdict).Synchronization lifecycle triggers handling debounced async payloads destined for ysdk.player.setData.Ensure code includes informative TypeScript documentation comments explaining how the Yandex SDK hooks interact with the engine boundaries.
